Uhmm. I thought so! I used the same thing. I'm currently  writing a wrapper over phonon because how it is now is more of a librarie suite then a full fledged framework. This is awesome because you can use only the libs you want!

What i'm trying to polish right now is the following format
```
phonon.module('module_name', function(ph) {    
   //code goes here
   //ph - internal facade for module "module_name" with phonon libraries and stuff such as html context and what ever else it's needed here :)
   - or -
   //ph - will have only two instructions require and instance

    //v1
    var ajax = ph.ajax({/* config */});

    //v2
    var ajax = ph.require('ajax');
    // if case
    var instance = ph.instance('some_lib_with_instance'); //This of course will held the local scope of "module_name ;)"  

    // on both v1 and v2
    ph.name -> "module_name"
    ph.DOM -> html component of this module
})
```

What do you think?
